----

''The parties in the elections to the European Parliament of June 2004 and their positions on software patents and other information infrastructure issues.''

 * EDD '' [[http://www.j.dk''|June Movement]]: strong and active opposition against software patents, severe scrutiny of EU legislation in general
   * [[BentHindrupAndersenEn| Bent Hindrup Andersen]]
 * Greens: strong opposition against software patentability (as part of Eurogreens)
 * LEFT: Pernille Frahm: strong and active opposition againt software patentability
 * Overview over many danish candidates and their opinion regarding software patents at http://www.it-pol.dk/Members/flemming/undersoegelse (notice that candidates voting no is listed as "Ja" in the table!)
 * Liberals (Venstre): Blindly follow DKPTO except for a few enligthened. (ruling party, forms government with conservative)
 * Conservative: Responsible minister is conservative. Blindly follow DKPTO.
 * [[DkSocDemEn| Social democrats]]: Has avoided the issue. Large party and winner of EU-parliament election.
